Founded in 1927, the Volvo Group is committed to driving prosperity and
shaping the future landscape through sustainable transport, mobility, and
infrastructure solutions. By offering trucks, buses, construction equipment,
power solutions for marine and industrial applications, financing and services
that increase our customers' uptime and productivity.  
  
Our headquarters are in Gothenburg, Sweden. Volvo Group shares are listed on
Nasdaq Stockholm.

  
  

** Transport is at the core of modern society. Imagine using your expertise to shape sustainable transport solutions for the future? If you seek to make a difference on a global scale, working with next-gen technologies and the sharpest collaborative teams, then we could be a perfect match. **

** What you will do **

At Volvo Group Australia, you will contribute to the transformation of our
company, the transport industry and society at large. As an IT Business
Analyst in the Digital & IT team, you will be responsible for but not limited
to:

  * Facilitating modelling and analysis of business processes and operations 
  * Designing concepts for various products 
  * Taking the lead in Business Analyst activities for the solutions in scope 
  * Identifying risks regarding the functional solution from a BA perspective, and propose changes when necessary 
  * Executing training together with the process and solution key users, and Business Process Developer 
  * Driving and coordinating small activities and projects delivered locally (but may be in collaboration with the Global IT team) 
** Your future team **

This role will be a 12 month fixed term contract, working alongside two other
Business Analysts and reporting to the Business Solutions Manager. The
Business Analysts are part of the greater Business Solutions team of 9,
including a Data Analyst, Business Systems Specialists and Master Data
Specialists. The Business Solutions team are a good-humoured and supportive
group, who keep their team strong with regular lunches and bonding activities.

** Who are you? **

Do you dream big? We do too, and we are excited to grow together. In this
role, you will bring:

  * A degree or qualification in IT (or related field) 
  * At least 12 months of working experience in a Business Analyst role 
  * Proven experience working with business process modelling tools 
  * Excellent communication skills and enjoy a customer facing role 
  * The ability to work well in a fast-paced environment 
  * A true team player attitude, willing to help out your team when needed 
** What's in it for you? **

We offer a solid package of compensation and benefits, plus you will enjoy:

  * We care about our people, we are committed to making your workplace safe and facilitate a healthier lifestyle for our employees through work life balance 
  * Access for you and your family to free, anonymous mental health support through our EAP - Sonder 
  * Modern offices with on-site parking and caf√© 
  * Opportunity to purchase an extra week of annual leave 
  * The potential for other Volvo opportunities on completion of the 12 month contract 
  * A Manager who encourages team activities to create an inclusive working environment 
** Ready for the next move? **

If you want to make a real impact in your career, the transportation business
is where you want to be. We look forward to meeting you.

We value your data privacy and therefore do not accept applications via mail.

** Who we are and what we believe in **   
Our focus on Inclusion, Diversity, and Equity allows each of us the
opportunity to bring our full authentic self to work and thrive by providing a
safe and supportive environment, free of harassment and discrimination. We are
committed to removing the barriers to entry, which is why we ask that even if
you feel you may not meet every qualification on the job description, please
apply and let us decide.

Applying to this job offers you the opportunity to join ** Volvo Group. **
Every day, across the globe, our trucks, buses, engines, construction
equipment, financial services, and solutions make modern life possible. We are
almost 100,000 people empowered to shape the future landscape of efficient,
safe and sustainable transport solutions. Fulfilling our mission creates
countless career opportunities for talents with sharp minds and passion across
the group's leading brands and entities.

** Group Digital & IT ** is the hub for digital development within Volvo Group. Imagine yourself working with cutting-edge technologies in a global team, represented in more than 30 countries. We are dedicated to leading the way of tomorrow's transport solutions, guided by a strong customer mindset and high level of curiosity, both as individuals and as a team. Here, you will thrive in your career in an environment where your voice is heard and your ideas matter. 

